<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <title>Use cases - ghostanalytics</title>
    <meta name="description" content="How different teams put ghostanalytics to work: SaaS, ecommerce, agencies, publishers, and developers. The same cookieless script, from a solo blog to a funded product.">
    <meta name="theme-color" content="#0a0c0e">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Geist:wght@400;500;600;700;800&family=Geist+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/marketing.css">
  </head>
  <body>
    @include('site-nav')

    <main>
      <nav class="shell subnav" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span>
        <span>Use cases</span>
      </nav>

      <section class="feat-hero shell">
        <span class="kicker">Use cases</span>
        <h1>Real numbers for teams that respect their visitors.</h1>
        <p>The same cookieless script fits a solo blog or a funded SaaS. Here is how different teams put ghostanalytics to work, and which features carry the weight.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a class="btn primary" href="/#install">Get your script tag</a>
          <a class="btn ghost" href="/dashboard">See a live dashboard</a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="reveal section shell" aria-label="Use cases">
        <div class="usecases">

          <a class="usecase" href="/use-cases/saas" data-no-router>
            <img src="https://picsum.photos/seed/ghost-saas-product-team/720/340" alt="A product team reviewing activation charts" width="720" height="340" loading="lazy">
            <div class="usecase-body">
              <h3>SaaS</h3>
              <p>Follow visitors from landing page to signup and activation, and attribute each account to the channel that earned it. No consent banner between a first-time visitor and your call to action.</p>
              <span class="textlink">Analytics for SaaS</span>
            </div>
          </a>

          <a class="usecase" href="/use-cases/ecommerce" data-no-router>
            <img src="https://picsum.photos/seed/ghost-ecommerce-storefront/720/340" alt="An online store checkout on a laptop" width="720" height="340" loading="lazy">
            <div class="usecase-body">
              <h3>Ecommerce</h3>
              <p>Tie carts, checkouts, and revenue back to the campaigns that drove them, with numbers that match your store. Your customer data never flows into an ad graph you do not control.</p>
              <span class="textlink">Analytics for ecommerce</span>
            </div>
          </a>

          <a class="usecase" href="/use-cases/agencies" data-no-router>
            <img src="https://picsum.photos/seed/ghost-agency-studio-desk/720/340" alt="An agency desk with client dashboards" width="720" height="340" loading="lazy">
            <div class="usecase-body">
              <h3>Agencies</h3>
              <p>Run every client site from one login and share a clean, read-only report in a single link. Exact data that stays in your own database, free of the sampling that makes agency reports hard to defend.</p>
              <span class="textlink">Analytics for agencies</span>
            </div>
          </a>

          <a class="usecase" href="/use-cases/publishers" data-no-router>
            <img src="https://picsum.photos/seed/ghost-publisher-newsroom/720/340" alt="A publisher reviewing article performance" width="720" height="340" loading="lazy">
            <div class="usecase-body">
              <h3>Publishers &amp; blogs</h3>
              <p>See which posts hold attention and where a spike came from, counted exactly rather than sampled. Core Web Vitals sit beside each article, so a slow page never quietly loses its audience.</p>
              <span class="textlink">Analytics for publishers</span>
            </div>
          </a>

          <a class="usecase" href="/use-cases/developers" data-no-router>
            <img src="https://picsum.photos/seed/ghost-open-source-terminal/720/340" alt="A terminal with a self-hosting command" width="720" height="340" loading="lazy">
            <div class="usecase-body">
              <h3>Developers</h3>
              <p>A one-line script, a one-function events API, and a clean HTTP endpoint to read it all back. Self-hostable, SingleStore-backed, and privacy-first by default. Your data stays yours.</p>
              <span class="textlink">Analytics for developers</span>
            </div>
          </a>

        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="reveal section shell" aria-label="Get started">
        <div class="cta-band">
          <h2>Your numbers. Your visitors' privacy. Both intact.</h2>
          <div class="cta-actions">
            <a class="btn primary" href="/#install">Get your script tag</a>
            <a class="btn ghost" href="/dashboard">See a live dashboard</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="footer shell">
      <div class="footer-bottom" style="border-top: none">
        <a class="brand" href="/" aria-label="ghostanalytics home">
          <span class="brand-mark">g</span>
          <span class="brand-name">ghostanalytics</span>
        </a>
        <span>No cookies. No personal data. Powered by Stacks and SingleStore.</span>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
